<!--
    Hausa (Hausa) — ha
    Script : Latin (Boko orthography), the standard written form; LTR.
             A traditional Arabic-based script (Ajami) exists but is not used
             in modern digital contexts; Boko is the sole orthography here.
    Approx.: ~80 M L1+L2 speakers (Nigeria, Niger, Ghana, Sudan; lingua franca
             across West and Central Africa).
    Register: Standard Modern Hausa as used in broadcast media and formal writing.
    Notes  : Hausa has grammatical gender (masculine/feminine) and a tonal system;
             tonal diacritics are NOT used in standard written Boko and are
             omitted here.  "Binge drinking" → shan giya da yawa / shan giya
             sosai — the latter phrase (sosai = excessively/very much) is used.
    Source : Translated from values-de/strings.xml (German source of truth).
-->
